			<subsubsection xml:id="prepare-the-data-for-analysis.">
				<title>Prepare the data for analysis.</title>

				<p>
					The data is prepared given the variables have already been converted into factor variables.
				</p>

				<p>
					Commentary: The variables of interest here are <c>defendant_race</c> and <c>penalty</c> which have already been converted into factor variables. Do not attempt to use the <c>factor</c> command to convert variables that are already factor variables as that will mess up that variable.
				</p>

			</subsubsection>

			<subsubsection xml:id="make-tables-or-plots-to-explore-the-data-visually.">
				<title>Make tables or plots to explore the data visually.</title>

				<p>
					The following table shows the breakdown of penalty in columns by defendant race in rows. We save this table to perform a Chi-Square Independence test.
				</p>

				<pre>defendant_penalty_table &lt;- tally(penalty ~ defendant_race, data=DPenalty)
defendant_penalty_table</pre>

				<pre>##        defendant_race
## penalty Black White
##   Death    17    19
##   Not     149   141</pre>

				<p>
					Here is an alternative view of the table with percentages by column.
				</p>

				<pre>tally(penalty ~ defendant_race, data=DPenalty, margins = TRUE, format= "percent")</pre>

				<pre>##        defendant_race
## penalty     Black     White
##   Death  10.24096  11.87500
##   Not    89.75904  88.12500
##   Total 100.00000 100.00000</pre>

			</subsubsection>
